The President will be delivering remarks in Cleveland, Ohio, outlining a set of targeted initiatives to support economic recovery and ensure long-term sustainable growth. The speech will be held at the Cuyahoga Community College West Campus and will be attended by approximately 800 students, faculty, and invited guests. The article also mentions some background information on the Recovery Act investments in Ohio and the Cleveland area. The pre-program will include an invocation by Reverend Otis Moss, Jr., the Pledge of Allegiance led by Duane Evans, an Iraq veteran and president of the Veterans Club at Cuyahoga Community College, and the National Anthem sung by Kira Seaton, an Assistant Professor of Music at Cuyahoga Community College. Several elected officials, including Governor Ted Strickland, Lieutenant Governor Lee Fisher, Senator Sherrod Brown, and various representatives and mayors, are expected to attend the event.